[normal] they have got more to start with”.  I just wonder, therefore, what your thoughts would be about 
[normal]whether it is time to have a local government equivalent of
[normal] the Office for Budget Responsibility.  That would then settle it, would it not?  Would you 
[normal]support that?
[normal]Brandon Lewis[bold]: I do not think there is anything to settle.  I appreciate you do not
[normal] know the spending power for Derby at the moment, but I think you will find, if you look at it, it is much higher than West Oxfordshire in the first place.  That is quite a simple fact.  It is the same for 
[normal]Newcastle
[normal], Liverpoo
[normal]l
[normal], Leeds and 
[normal]Manchester
[normal]; they are much higher than the more affluent areas.  
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]Q18 [bold]&#xa0;&#xa0; 
