[normal], though, about a local government equivalent of the Office for Budget 
[normal]Responsibility?
[normal]Brandon Lewis[bold]: 
[normal]The problem is y
[normal]ou are also looking at it from the point of view of the
[normal] grant settlement.  Bear in mind, of course, 70% of local authorities’ money—it used to be 50%—now is locally derived.  That will 
[normal]hopefully grow as we see economic growth.  You also have to bear in 
[normal]mind we are working within a constrict in which we are having to reduce the deficit and pay down, eventually, the debt that was inherited from the last Government.  T
[normal]he Secretary of State 
[normal]made the point to you
[normal] last w
[normal]e
[normal]ek
[normal] that
[normal], with local government accounting for
[normal] about a quarter of all 
[normal]Government expenditure, it has a big part to play.  If the authorities that are getting the largest part of the grant are losing 2.9% of their funding, in cash terms that will be a different figure compared 
[normal]with 
[normal]some
[normal]where 
[normal]that gets a much smaller grant in the first place.
